result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: 9:35 am cases called-15CF80, 15CF107, & 15TR1404-Defendant Sheena M Gumz in court with attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached with argued sentence stated on record.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Count 1 of 15CF80.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright Count 2 of 15CF80 & Dismisses and reads-in Counts 3 & 4 of 15CF80, 15CF107 & 15TR1404. Argument by ADA Anderson. Argument by Attorney Zamzow. Statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: 7 months WCJ, with Huber and Good Time Credit, to commence forthwith.  Credit for 99 days served. $1900 fine inclusive of costs, to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Attorney Zamzow fees to be paid. $42.50 Blood draw fee. 30 mo DL revocation, 2 year IID, effective today. AODA and follow through.    Maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. DNA sample & surcharge. Term of Agent. Appeal Rights Given. Court orders cash bond to be applied.
from Atty Zamzow Re: Request to Adjourn 9/29/2015 P/S - Request granted by the Court

15CF107, 15CF80, & 15TR1404 NOT PUT ON THE RECORD: Attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Zamzow requests additional time to discuss options with the defendant. Court set matter for Plea/sentencing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 29, 2015 at 01:00 pm.

3:28 pm case called. Defendant Sheena M. Gumz in court with attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow, by phone.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Court questions defendant regarding appearance of Attorney Zamzow by phone-defendant confirms request for Attorney Zamzow to appear by phone. Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Preliminary Hearing and Time Limits discussed. Defendant wishes to waive time limits for preliminary hearing. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of time limits for preliminary hearing.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Status conference scheduled for August 18, 2015 at 11:30 am.
from Defendant to Judge Dutcher - Copies distributed by Deputy Clerk to DA and Atty Jeanne Zamzow

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Defendant is prohibited from being in possession of any dangerous weapons.

Case called @ 1:12 p.m. Defendant Sheena M. Gumz in court, in custody, appears via video.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant wishes to have counsel. DA Blader requesting $500 Cash Bond. Statement by the defendant regarding bond. Court orders $500 Cash Bond. Court orders attorney to be appointed forthwith. IA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Initial appearance scheduled for July 22, 2015 at 03:15 pm.
